org.openhab.binding.velux.internal

Class VeluxBindingProperties

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.VeluxBindingProperties

  • @NonNullByDefault
public class VeluxBindingProperties
extends java.lang.Object
    The VeluxBindingProperties class defines common constants, which are used within the property definitions. This class contains the property identifications:
    • PROPERTY_BINDING_BUNDLEVERSION for identification of the binding,
    • PROPERTY_BINDING_NOOFBRIDGES for number of bridges,
    • PROPERTY_BINDING_NOOFTHINGS for number of things,
    • PROPERTY_SCENE_NAME for defining the name of a scene,
    • PROPERTY_SCENE_VELOCITY for defining the velocity of a scene,
    • CONFIG_ACTUATOR_SERIALNUMBER for defining the serial number of an actuator, a rollershutter and a window,
    • PROPERTY_ACTUATOR_NAME for defining the name of an actuator, a rollershutter and a window,
    • PROPERTY_ACTUATOR_INVERTED for modifying the value of a Channel,
    • PROPERTY_VSHUTTER_SCENELEVELS for defining a virtual shutter.
    • PROPERTY_VSHUTTER_CURRENTLEVEL for defining a virtual shutter.
    Author:
    Guenther Schreiner - Initial contribution
